article.headline: Hartford 66, Yale 65 (OT)
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. (AP) -- Joe Zeglinski hit two free throws with 1:17 remaining in overtime to help Hartford defeat Yale 66-65 on Monday night. Zeglinski finished with a game-high 18 points while Bo Taylor scored 15 of his 17 points in the second half. Hartford (5-4) overcame a 15-point second-half deficit to tie the game at 58 at the end of regulation. The Bulldogs' Eric Flato knocked down three first-half 3-pointers and finished with 17 points. His jumper for the win with three seconds remaining in overtime fell short. Yale (2-7) shot just 33 percent from the field in the second half after building a 12-point halftime lead. Nick Holmes also had 13 points for the Bulldogs, who played without captain Sam Kaplan. He broke his nose during the first half of Saturday's game against American.
